<h1>Enforcement Guide</h1>
<p><strong>{{brand_name}}</strong> - {{claim_label}}</p>

<hr>

<p>
  This guide is for the stage after judgment. It does not mean judgment has been granted.
</p>

<h2>If judgment is unpaid</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Check the judgment order and deadline for payment.</li>
  <li>Keep a record of any part payments or proposals.</li>
  <li>Consider which enforcement route best matches what is known about the defendant.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Common enforcement options</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Warrant or writ of control, where enforcement agents are appropriate.</li>
  <li>Attachment of earnings, where the defendant is employed.</li>
  <li>Third party debt order, where bank or debtor details are known.</li>
  <li>Charging order, where the defendant owns property.</li>
  <li>Order to obtain information, where more detail is needed about income or assets.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  Each enforcement step may require a further court form and fee. Check the current HMCTS instructions
  before applying.
</p>
